## Context

Child of tracker 0131 (Split Makefile by workpackage). The manuscript
writing workpackage is done (branch t0131-manuscript-wp): manuscript.mk
builds the Œconomia article clean-room from git-tracked deliverables with
no data, isolated via the `manuscript` Quarto profile. This ticket covers
the rest of 0131 for the other papers and the analysis-intermediate eviction.

## Relevant files
- `Makefile` — still defines render rules for corpus-report, technical-report,
  breakpoint-detect-method-zoo, data-paper, multilayer-detection (lines ~672+).
- `manuscript.mk`, `_quarto-manuscript.yml` — the pattern to replicate per paper.
- `.gitignore` — ignore-then-negate block for `content/{figures,tables}`.
- `content/tables/tab_lexical_tfidf.csv` (35 MB), `tab_pole_papers.csv` (3.8 MB),
  `qa_type_report.csv` (3.7 MB) — analysis intermediates living under content/tables/.

## Actions
1. Per remaining paper, extract a `<wp>.mk` (datapaper.mk, techrep.mk,
   companion/multilayer, ncc) plus a `_quarto-<wp>.yml` profile that excludes
   sibling docs, mirroring manuscript.mk. Each builds clean-room from committed
   deliverables only.
2. git-track each paper's small byte-stable writing deliverables (figures +
   tables) via .gitignore negations, like the manuscript's 3 PNGs + tab_venues.md.
   Note: tab_corpus_sources.md / tab_languages.md / tab_citation_coverage.md are
   the data-paper/techrep includes — they belong to those slices, not the manuscript.
3. 0131 action 8 — evict the large analysis intermediates (tab_lexical_tfidf.csv,
   tab_pole_papers.csv, qa_type_report.csv, …) out of content/tables/ into an
   analysis-side derived/scratch dir; update producing + consuming Make targets.
4. Keep DVC scoped to genuine corpus data.

## Test
For each remaining writing workpackage: in a data-less worktree, run
`make -f <wp>.mk output/content/<doc>.pdf` and confirm the PDF builds with
only Quarto + TeX (no uv, no data) — the proof manuscript.mk already passes.

## Invariants
- `make papers` from the full Makefile still builds all docs (with data).
- Per-target QUARTO_PROFILE export (not file-scope) so profiles don't leak.

## Exit criteria
- One `<wp>.mk` + profile per remaining paper, each buildable clean-room.
- Analysis intermediates evicted from content/tables/; targets updated.
- Writing-toolchain spec documented in README (0131 exit criterion 4,
  re-homed here): the clean-room writing build needs only Quarto + TeX Live
  + Pandoc — no `uv`, no `dvc` client, no data (0131 action 9 scoped DVC to
  corpus data only).

Parent tracker: tickets/0131-split-build-by-workpackage.erg (CLOSED #948 —
0131 closed rather than held open as a single-child pseudo-tracker; this
ticket carries all remaining scope).
